		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I finally got around to finishing this game that I started a couple years back, I think it was. Details on how to play are in the game. I haven't talked to the website owner about soliciting for donations, so I'll just skip that part. In case there are folks that don't get to the credits at the end of the game, I would like to mention that the sound engine is DragNSF1. Thanks Drag : )
<br />
<br /><a href="http://robertlbryant.com/download/NES_Virus_Cleaner.nes" class="postlink">Download NES Virus Cleaner</a>
<br />
<br />Hope you like it!
<br />
<br />EDIT: Source code can now be found <a href="http://robertlbryant.com/index.php/gaming/development/nes-virus-cleaner/" class="postlink">here</a>.

		

